{"key":"processedPost-6849875","value":{"id":6849875,"first":6849365,"last":6870879,"when":1177882529,"utime":"04/30/07 12:35 AM","content":"You still have glare.  Never hold a jar in your hand to take pictures.  It's hard enough to hold a camera still, and it's hard to hold a jar still, but trying to do both amplifies the movement.  Use a tripod or a book to set the camera on, ditto for the jar, and then use a light other than the camera flash to take the picture.  All a flash does is relfect light back into the camera lense.<br /><br />This is what a picture of a colonizing jar should look like.<br />RR<br /><br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-10/329565823-colonizing_brf_jars_004a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/07-10/329565823-thumb_colonizing_brf_jars_004a.jpg\"></a>","title":"Re: ? for RR regarding Mycelium Culture","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}